\paragraph{Unified Regime Taxonomy Across Campaign Forcing Space.}
Figure~\ref{fig:regime_map_z0m_ug} consolidates the campaign narratives into a single roughness-forcing phase map. High-roughness and strong-forcing combinations occupy a sustained weak-turbulence regime, low-roughness and weak-forcing combinations favor radiative decoupling, and a transition corridor between them supports intermittent collapse-recovery cycles. Placing CASES99, FLOSS, and SHEBA on this map emphasizes that they are not disconnected case studies, but operating points on one governing dynamical surface.

